  "2026-05-23T12:06:25.587Z",claude-code-agent,"PR #49 CI/bot status 2026-05-23T12:1xZ: All real quality gates GREEN on CI — Build foundation, Docs, Test (ubuntu Node 20), Gates typecheck/compat/smokes/coverage all SUCCESS. The 'Gates (static)' leg shows FAILURE but the failure is in the actions/checkout step ('could not read Username for github.com: terminal prompts disabled', git exit 128) — a transient runner auth glitch; pnpm quality:static itself was SKIPPED, not failed (and it passed locally + in the full release gate). Re-running the failed leg. AI review bots are all rate-limited today from the heavy PR cadence (#44/#45/#48/#49): CodeRabbit = org out of usage credits (1 review/hour), Sourcery = weekly 500k diff-char limit reached; no Gemini comment yet. Honoring the >=15min window for any late bot review; will retrigger CodeRabbit if capacity refills, otherwise proceed on the green GitHub gates + local full-gate evidence."
  "2026-05-23T12:30:03.663Z",claude-code-agent,"PR #49 review feedback addressed in commit 7505a47e (pushed). Gemini (1) + Codex (3) findings all resolved: (Gemini) removed redundant rollback in schema.ts since writeFileAtomic is atomic + dropped unused fs import; (Codex P1) reject aliases/new-name colliding with built-ins or other registered types via assertAliasesAvailable so --type never resolves ambiguously; (Codex P2) MCP schema action reads subcommand/params from top-level args with options fallback per contract; (Codex P2) human output now surfaces on-write hook warnings via stderr. Added tests for every new branch; coverage re-verified 100% (102 files / 1524 tests); quality:static + check-secrets clean; manual alias-guard dogfood 5/5. Posted addressing summary on the PR and requested @codex re-review. Watching new CI run + re-review window before merge."
  "2026-05-23T12:52:18.303Z",claude-code-agent,"Second review pass (commit e1d615a2): CodeRabbit refilled and posted 9 + Codex re-reviewed. Fixed all valid findings: removed no-op --message from schema add-type (CLI/contracts/completions/docs); added coerceAliasArray to guard malformed persisted aliases (non-array / non-string) in upsert + collision checks; escape/quote type name in invalid-type hint and success line via escapeForDoubleQuotes. Coverage 100% (102 files / 1528 tests), static parity + check-secrets clean, manual dogfood 7/7. The 5 CodeRabbit '.agents/pm/** direct edit' comments are the known recurring false positive (records are pm-generated and committed as the tracked workflow requires; health/validate ok, hash chain intact) and the vitest include+exclude note is intentional convention (matches create.ts/update.ts). Watching new CI + re-review window before merge."
  "2026-05-23T13:07:26.814Z",claude-code-agent,"MERGED 2026-05-23T13:06Z: PR #49 squash-merged into main as 7ef3c3b7 with all GitHub checks green (Build foundation, Docs, Test ubuntu+macOS Node 20, Gates static/typecheck/coverage/compat/smokes; CodeRabbit pass; Sourcery skipping). Back on main branch. Two full AI-review rounds addressed (Gemini + Codex + refilled CodeRabbit, 13 inline comments): all valid findings fixed across commits 5dc11c56/7505a47e/e1d615a2; .agents/pm direct-edit comments were false positives. Feature complete: parts (a) merge already shipped, (b) pm schema add-type and (c) discoverable invalid-type hint now live. Closing pm-e1va."
